cket Conversations Session One\n|\nI have no idea what my best material is. Different people like different things. I'll say this: The political stuff gets the press, but the relationship jokes sell all the seats.\n\n- Chris\n|\nMy mom is a wonderful woman. She's always been an inspiration to me, but having kids helped me make even more sense of my relationship with her.\n\n- Britney\n|\nAs per the law of karma, that which is your meat today, this dear beloved animal will make mincemeat of you tomorrow. In another birth.\n\n- Fakeer\n|\nAfter death something new begins, over which all powers of the world of death have no more might.\n\n- Dietrich\n|\nHell, yeah, Ryland. Man up and carpe girl.\n\n- John Corwin, Dark Light of Mine\n|\nIf you are distressed by anything external, the pain is not due to the thing itself, but to your estimate of it; and this you have the power to revoke at any moment.\n\n- Marcus Aurelius, Meditations\n|\nWhen you reach out to those in need, do not be surprised if the essential meaning of something occurs.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nNo matter what has happened, you too have the power to enjoy yourself.\n\n- Allen\n|\nJudgement is always based on experience and sometimes you will battle a person's history first, before commonsense will ever win the war.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nIf you can honor yourself and be real about your discomfort and pain, then your happiness will be just as real.\n\n- Bryant McGill, Simple Reminders: Inspiration for Living Your Best Life\n|\nTo overcome the fear of failure, do what makes you fearful.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI do tasks for the gods, usually things like tracking down rare items or taking someone safely to a destination.'D'Molay the Freeman Tracker\n\n- M. Scott Verne, City of the Gods: Forgotten\n|\nHaving a vision is great,but don’t be so focused onyour next goal that you forgetto enjoy your achievements.\n\n- Domonique Bertolucci, The Happiness Code: Ten Keys to Being the Best You Can Be\n|\nThere will be grace and forgiveness enough, old dog, even for you. I pray you will spare me a drink from that cup, when it overflows for you.- Miles Vorkosigan\n\n- Lois McMaster Bujold, The Warrior's Apprentice\n|\nSomewhere, someone is search for the pieces of you that mold well with theirs.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nBut never had their youthful beauty seemed so pure and high, as when its glow was chastened by adversity.\n\n- Nathaniel Hawthorne, Young Goodman Brown and Other Short Stories\n|\nMost of our life we pass by waiting for tomorrow, but not living for today.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nHe'd been told that women were sensitive about such things, as if a scar could somehow ruin their beauty, but scars were just stories told in flesh...\n\n- Larry\n|\nOf all the gifts you can get, friends and family are the best!\n\n- Jan Britland, The Adventures of Rodger Dodger Dog Activities Book\n|\nI am a fool with a heart but no brains, and you are a fool with brains but no heart; and we’re both unhappy, and we both suffer.\n\n- Fyodor Dostoyevsky, The Idiot\n|\nWhen you give a present,you're giving with your heart.Never give thinking of money,or your gift will fall apart.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nHe wished to please everybody,' Franklin later said of Keith, 'and having little to give, he gave expectations.\n\n- Walter Isaacson, Benjamin Franklin: An American Life\n|\nYou don't pray for the growth and success of the organization you work for, but you pray God favours you before your boss.Really?\n\n- Faithful\n|\nSensationalism dies quickly, fear is long-lived.\n\n- Agatha Christie, Death in the Clouds\n|\nA lot of my childhood memories involve walking home in floods of tears. At that age, feeling unpopular is difficult to handle.\n\n- Rachel\n|\nYou know, people can't fall in love with me just because I'm good at what I do.\n\n- Robert\n|\nI want to show everyone that if you pursue your dreams, they can come true no matter what. That's what I want to do.\n\n- Martin\n|\nBeing an unveiled wife is about confronting and crushing your fears; believing in truth more than in doubt, worry, or lies, and finding your security in God alone\n\n- Jennifer       Smith, The Unveiled Wife: Embracing Intimacy with God and Your Husband\n|\nProximity to reality induces feelings of emptiness, horror and depression. Do not approach it alone.\n\n- Anthony Marais, Delusionism\n|\nThe world doesn't make sense, so why should I paint pictures that do?\n\n- Pablo\n|\nMaybe [aliens] have been in our lives a lot longer than we want to admit. People have always seen strange things—elves and fairies—and now we don't. Now we see them, right?\n\n- Thomm Quackenbush, Artificial Gods\n|\nFarewell, my great one, my own, farewell, my pride, farewell, my swift, deep, dear river, how I loved your daylong splashing, how I loved to plunge into your cold waves.\n\n- Boris Pasternak, Doctor Zhivago\n|\nIn the heart and in the soul, evil takes its wicked toll. When moonlight shines like flowing blood, over the earth, the Daimons will flood\n\n- Sherrilyn Kenyon, No Mercy\n|\nOnward boldly, pursue your passion.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nBut when I would see the surrogate, my first instinct, my first reaction would be jealousy, because she was doing what I wanted to do.\n\n- Cheryl\n|\nJust because she isn't human, do you think that means she doesn't feel pain?\n\n- Stephenie Meyer, The Host\n|\nHatred is the most accessible and comprehensive of all the unifying agents. Mass movements can rise and spread without belief in a god, but never without a belief in a devil.\n\n- Eric Hoffer, The True Believer: Thoughts on the Nature of Mass Movements"